    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-03T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/731: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-03T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 3, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. I have been told by a member of the British delegation that London had
                    telephoned the delegation to the effect that consideration was being given there
                    to an approach to Washington on the subject of the United States collaborating
                    in some form with the projected conversations relating to the 1906
                    treaty—Consulate’s 262, August 2, 4 p.m.<note n="48" xml:id="d503fn48">Not
                        printed.</note> paragraph 1 (2)—having an observer present being mentioned
                    as a possible form.</p>
                <p>While I was told this in a manner exceedingly casual I gained the impression that
                    it was with a view to obtaining my reaction. I naturally made no comment
                    whatsoever.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
